  "texts": [
    "As G A is a disjoint union of wheel graphs, G A is planar.",
    "The same argument shows that G B is planar (Extended Data Fig. 1b).",
    "The visualization of the [[144, 12, 12]] code in Fig. 1b shows the edges of G A and G B as dashed 'A' edges and solid 'B' edges, respectively.We leave optimization of the code layout satisfying specific hardware constraints for future work.",
    "For now, it is sufficient to note that any planar graph admits a planar embedding without edge crossings for any prescribed vertex locations, see for example theorem 1 in ref. 63.",
    "Moreover, this embedding can be efficiently computed 63."
